article.description: Nikita Bell scored 18 points to lead No. 12 North Carolina past North Carolina State, 80-59.
article.headline: Brown, Bell each score 12 in second half
article.linkText: North Carolina's big second half too much for N.C. State
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- Nikita Bell scored 12 of her 18 points
in the second half as North Carolina (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) pulled away from North
Carolina State en route to an 80-59 victory Sunday.

	   Coretta Brown also scored 12 in the second half and 17 overall,
and Leah Metcalf added 14 for North Carolina (12-1, 2-0 Atlantic
Coast Conference).

	   Kaayla Chones led N.C. State (6-7, 1-1) with 16 points and 10
rebounds for her fourth double-double this season and the 17th of
her career.

	   Brown scored nine points during North Carolina's 19-3 run that
put the game away. She went 4-for-6 on 3-pointers, and made one to
give North Carolina a 75-52 lead with 3:08 to play.

	   North Carolina held the Wolfpack to 7-for-27 shooting in the
first half and led 35-25 at the break.

	   N.C. State went 10:49 without a field goal during a first-half
stretch, allowing North Carolina to turn a 14-14 tie into a 28-17
lead.

	   N.C. State had just one field goal during a 6:02 span of the
second half as the Tar Heels went on their decisive run.
